cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and word embeddings. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper presents a method for affordance extraction that can be applied to reinforcement learning agents. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper involves training word embeddings and using linear algebra for querying. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a less likely category, but the paper does touch on the idea of common knowledge and how it can be used to improve agent performance. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a less likely category, but the paper does involve querying a database of word embeddings to extract affordances.
